{
    "name": "Lisavet",
    "type": "npc",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Lisavet, Well-Read Acolyte",
            "type": "section",
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "No-Prep Character: Lisavet",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "No-Prep Character: Lisavet pg. 0",
                        "alt": "No-Prep Character: Lisavet pg. 0",
                        "href": "https://paizo.com/community/blog/v5748dyo6shk1"
                    },
                    "page": 0
                }
            ],
            "html": "Lisavet found two callings in the Dawnflower Library. She was not only drawn to the faith of <a aonid=\"16\" game-obj=\"Deities\">Sarenrae</a>, benevolent goddess of the sun and healing, but also adored the numerous and varied books within the library. Although trained as a healer, she spent most of her time reading adventure stories. When the opportunity came for adventure of her own, Lisavet put her self-doubt aside and embraced her faith, becoming a righteous hero. Lisavet's adventures are described in <i>The Shroud of Four Silences</i>.<br/><br/> Lisavet is just the sort of person anyone would want to find at a local shrine or hospital: caring, intelligent, and eager to provide whatever assistance she can. Although she puts on a greater show of confidence than she sometimes feels, she knows that Sarenrae will never let her down.<br/><br/><b><u><a aonid=\"5\" game-obj=\"Skills\" general=\"true\">Recall Knowledge - Humanoid</a></u> (<u><a aonid=\"14\" game-obj=\"Skills\">Society</a></u>)</b>: DC 26"
        }
    ],
